  "prompt": "Who is the favorite to win the Gold Medal in Men's football in the Rio 2016 Olympics?",
  "response": "At the **2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics**, the **Brazil national under-23 football team** won the **gold medal** in men's football. They secured the title by defeating **Germany** in the final match through a **5-4 penalty shootout** after the game ended in a **1-1 draw** during regular and extra time.\n\n**Prior to the tournament**, several teams were considered favorites to win the gold medal, including:\n\n1. **Brazil**: As the host nation with a strong footballing tradition, Brazil was always seen as a top contender.\n2. **Germany**: Known for their disciplined and talented squads, Germany was another favorite.\n3. **Nigeria**: With a history of success in youth tournaments, Nigeria was expected to perform well.\n4. **Japan**: They had shown great potential in previous competitions and were considered dark horses.\n\nUltimately, Brazil lived up to expectations by capturing the gold medal on their home soil.",
